  <!-- Auto-Formatting Section -->
  <section>
    <h2 id="auto-formatting">Auto-Formatting (data-format-date)</h2>
    <p>VB provides locale-aware date formatting via the <code>data-format-date</code> attribute. Like <a href="/docs/elements/native/data/"><code>&lt;data&gt;</code></a>'s <code>data-format-number</code>, the visible text serves as a no-JS fallback and is replaced with formatted output on init.</p>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Attribute Value</th><th>Output (en-US)</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>data-format-date</code> (empty)</td><td>Feb 9, 2026 (medium)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-format-date="short"</code></td><td>2/9/26</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-format-date="long"</code></td><td>February 9, 2026</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-format-date="full"</code></td><td>Monday, February 9, 2026</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>data-format-date="relative"</code></td><td>2 days ago</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>Add <code>data-format-time</code> for time display (<code>short</code>, <code>medium</code>, <code>long</code>, <code>full</code>). Override locale per-element with <code>data-locale</code>. See the <a href="/docs/i18n/">i18n guide</a> for locale resolution.</p>
  </section>

